<TITLE> BB to take up first 5 year plan from 2010 </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, July 21 (bdnews24.com)Bangladesh Bank is preparing its first-ever long-term plan to boost the stagnant banking sector, central bank governor Atiur Rahman said on Tuesday. "A five-year strategic plan will lift the sector through consistent monetary policy, greater automation, increasing manpower skills, reducing lending rates and, overall, finding the proper approach for banks to contribute more to the growth of the economy," Rahman told bdnews24.com. "This sort of five-year planning is going to be introduced for the first time in the banking sector," he said. The plan will be finalised after discussions with the chiefs of public, private, special and foreign banks operating in the country. "The process is already underway," Rahman added. bdn
